Mayor Tony Vauss

It Is A Privilege To Serve As Irvington Mayor

As Mayor of Irvington, I pledged to lead and represent our township, collaborating with residents to shape its future and establish it as an Essex County exemplar. Proud of our three-year achievements, we remain focused on continuous progress through robust policies and teamwork, united by a common dream for Irvington.

TAX SALE WILL BE HELD DECEMBER 18, 2025 AT 9:00 AM

Friendly Reminder

Please be reminded that all outstanding municipal charges will be included in our annual tax sale.

On November 11 , all properties with delinquencies (due November 1 and prior) must be included in the accelerated tax sale and will be subject to additional fees as required by State law. For all delinquent payments received after November 10th, certified funds payable to the Township of Irvington ( ) will be required. options, and will be accepted. Please call 973-399-6613 for updated interest amounts due.

Pursuant to N.J.S.A 54:4-64, taxes are valid whether or not the taxpayer (or their authorized agent) receives a bill. The statutes indicate that the taxpayer is put on notice to ascertain from the proper official the amount of their tax or assessment liabilities. This statute applies to If you are having problems with receiving your bills, please notify your local Post Office.

Online payment options are suspended as of the (4:30 pm) on November 10 due to the townships annual tax sale process and will be reactivated after the tax sale is complete.

Please be advised that should your payments be returned for nonpayment for any reason (including rejected online payments, stop payments, NSF, etc.) you will be required to remit payments via certified funds only for a minimum of 1 (one) year.

Tax Sale: December 18, 2025

The Township of Irvington is an accelerated tax sale municipality.

It is the obligation of the tax collector to collect all property taxes, sewer, and other municipal charges in the year that they are due. This helps greatly reduce the reserve for uncollected taxes, helping to keep the tax levy flat.

As a courtesy, the Tax Collector mails delinquent reminder notices throughout the year. Due to limited timing,delinquent notices are not mailed for outstanding charges as of November 10 . Helpful information is also printed on the back of all tax bills.

To avoid the tax sale process, property owners must pay all municipal charges in full by November 10 . Unfortunately, postmarks cannot be honored.

The tax sale list will be published in a local paper, posted on the townships website, and posted in 5 public places. (N.J.S.A. 54:5-26) Once the tax sale is generated, a fee of $65-$150 is added to each delinquent account as required by state law and . The fee is comprised of a 2% cost of sale charge, with a minimum $15 and a maximum $100, and the cost of 2 tax sale mailings at $25 each. (N.J.S.A. 54:5-38, N.J.S.A. 54:5-26)
